{"title_page": "Ragnar Smedslund", "text_new": "'''Ragnar Smedslund''' (13 April 1900, [[Helsinki]] \u2013 1981) was a Finnish diplomat. He was Master of Philosophy and served as Consul General in [[Tokyo]] 1952\u20131957, as Ambassador 1957\u20131962. He was a negotiating officer of the [[Ministry for Foreign Affairs (Finland)|Ministry for Foreign Affairs]] since 1962, when he received the Special Envoy and the value of a sovereign minister.<ref name=oit>Otavan Iso tietosanakirja, Otava 1966, osa 7 p. 1581</ref> He was ambassador in [[Lisbon]] and [[Bern]] in 1965\u20131967.<ref>[http://www.finlandia.org.pt/public/default.aspx?nodeid=40741&contentlan=1&culture=fi-FI Edustuston historia]</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Smedslund, Ragnar}}\n[[Category:Ambassadors of Finland to Switzerland]]\n[[Category:Ambassadors of Finland to Japan]]\n[[Category:Ambassadors of Finland to Portugal]]\n\n\n{{diplomat-stub}}\n", "text_old": "'''Ragnar Smedslund''' (13 April 1900, [[Helsinki]] \u2013 1981) was a Finnish diplomat. He was Master of Philosophy and served as Consul General in [[Tokyo]] 1952-1957, as Ambassador 1957-1962. He was a negotiating officer of the [[Ministry for Foreign Affairs (Finland)|Ministry for Foreign Affairs]] since 1962, when he received the Special Envoy and the value of a sovereign minister.<ref name=oit>Otavan Iso tietosanakirja, Otava 1966, osa 7 p. 1581</ref> He was ambassador in [[Lisbon]] and [[Bern]] in 1965-1967.<ref>[http://www.finlandia.org.pt/public/default.aspx?nodeid=40741&contentlan=1&culture=fi-FI Edustuston historia]</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Smedslund, Ragnar}}\n[[Category:Ambassadors of Finland to Switzerland]]\n[[Category:Ambassadors of Finland to Japan]]\n[[Category:Ambassadors of Finland to Portugal]]\n\n\n{{diplomat-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Iridescent", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:Cleanup andtypo fixing,typo(s) fixed: 1952-1957 \u2192 1952\u20131957 (3)", "url_pag